<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880502-0184 </DOCNO><HL> General Housewares To Buy Knife Maker </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GHW </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> STAMFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Housewares Corp. said it agreed to buy closely held Chicago Cutlery Inc., a Minneapolis knife maker, in a transaction valued at about $30 million.    The payment would include 440,000 shares of General Housewares common. The shares currently are valued at $3.8 million based on General Housewares' closing price of $8.625 in New York Stock Exchange composite trading Friday.    The maker of cookware and gifts said the purchase is subject to various conditions but should close by mid-June. General Housewares currently has 2.4 million shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>